parameters: Warily entering the forest, you find an old path.
After breaking through some foliage, you see him:
Right in front of you, Nebula is waiting.
You attack, ready for the fight of your life!
Nebula's defeat lets out a large blastwave.
After you recover, you notice the trees open up to reveal...
A villager! In fact, ALL the villagers are in trees!
You quickly pull the unconscious people out, one by one.
You tend to the wounded as some of them begin to awake.
One by one, the villagers wake up, realizing they're safe.
You manage to get them all back on their feet.
Dawn breaks as they begin to clap and cheer...
You know, maybe this adventuring thing isn't so bad...
...If only you'd made the right choice beforehand...
But now, it's time to move on. More adventures await!
Perhaps this time, you could try a different approach?
You've reached the end, my friend.
It's time to close the game.
Perhaps, again, my friend,
We'll meet someday.
Every action has purpose,
And every purpose has an outcome.
Whether or not it seems on surface,
You're never the only one.

You are dropped off at a camp right outside the forest.
It seems like an old army camp that now houses, well...
Every race is there, except humans.
Sam and Willow are instructing their forces. Polly joins in.
Jake is at a table surrounded by commanding officers.
It seems they're marking various exits to the forest.
You hear a roar in the distance: The Dragon King, it seems.
Even Gate is here, serving food to hungry combatants.
Evil
Jake
"Alright, so we have all escape routes closed."
"Let's go over the plans with our hero..."
*He pulls up a seat for you* "Look, dude..."
"I'll be honest, we've NEVER faced a demon."
Evil
Jake
"Oh, crap! You were asleep! Let me explain..."
"That Nebula demon? The Mayor..."
"He didn't WORSHIP him, he IS him!"
"He's taken the entire village captive."
Evil
Jake
"He would have taken you, too, but your scent?"
"The Dragon King put the demon's scent on you."
"That made you invisible to his power."
"I guess he assumed you were out of town."
Evil
Jake
"Anyway, we're blocking his exits off."
"When you go in, we'll have you covered."
"The Dragons and Harpies have the skies."
"The Orcs and Goblins have the ground."
Evil
Jake
"If he gets out, the Slimes will use magic..."
"To slow him down, while us Minotaurs..."
"We take him out for good."
"Where do you come in, though?"
Evil
Jake
"YOU are plan A. I just described B and C."
"Drink this potion, it will help."
"You will obtain more strength..."
"And learn abilities needed for this fight."
As you drink the potion, a wave of warmth flows over you.
Then a cool breeze, then blistering heat, ice cold, and...
Then it suddenly stops. Your body is more muscular.
Your brain contains knowledge it didn't before.
You ready your gear and take off into the forest.
Above you, you can see the Dragon King circling.
Each of his mates have riders, while he doesn't.
He swoops down and speaks briefly:
Monster
Dragon King
"Good luck out there. I'm here if you need."
*He takes to the skies again*
Breaking through some foliage, you see...
Nebula. Staring right at you.
IT'S TIME TO END THIS!
SF_Monster
Nebula
"FOOL! YOU THINK ME DEFEATED?"
"I WILL SHOW YOU THE POWER OF A DEMON LORD!"
*He creates a large, powerful energy beam*
*He laughs as you scramble to get away*
Monster
Dragon King
"YOU WILL NOT TAKE ANOTHER LIFE, MONSTER!"
*He swoops down, not caring about the beam*
*He starts clawing and biting Nebula*
*Finally, as Nebula's armor cracks, he feasts*
As the last of Nebula's body disappears...
The Dragon King belches hot, foul smoke.
He then falls to the ground, his wounds apparent.
You rush to help him, tears in your eyes.
Monster
Dragon King
"Do not..." *gasp* "weep, diplomat..."
"I did this of my own accord..."
"The Dragons end here, surrounded by beloveds."
"I couldn't imagine" *gasp* "a better death..."
You look around, helpless. All the races are converging.
Most of them saw what happened. They stand in solidarity.
Polly weeps, Sam and Willow hold each other, crying...
And Jake wipes a tear from his eye.
The Dragon Mates mourn loudly at the death of their race.
You look back at the King, slowly passing away.
The corruption from the beam and the demon are taking hold.
You cry louder than you ever have before. Wailing cries.
Gate
Gate
"Alright, alright, move people!"
"Geeze, and I thought Slimes were bad!"
*Gate moves quickly through the crowd*
*They're trailed by a large group of Slimes*
Gate
Gate
"It's OK, ohshubi, there's no need to cry."
"You have Slimes on your side!"
*They notice your confusion and sigh*
"Time, magic, and water, remember?"
Gate
Gate
"Release a little of this, a little of that..."
"We'll be sloppy-looking for a bit..."
"But anything for you, Ohshubi."
*They smile at you reassuringly*
Gate
Gate
"OK, my Slimey friends! Hop to it!"
"We need every inch of this Dragon covered!"
"Remember not to turn it back TOO far..."
"Just enough to heal the damage, got it?"
The Slimes quickly move to cover every part of the King.
He's breathing heavily, barely holding on to life.
You step back, praying to whatever powers may be.
The Slimes glow an purple-pink color. The color of magic.
Your head gets dizzy as it glows brighter, and brighter.
With one last flash, it dissipates, leaving behind...
The Dragon King, fully restored, and very wet.
The Slimes move away, each slightly smaller than before.
Gate makes their way back into the crowd.
You notice them walk up to Polly and hug her.
In the corner of your eye, Sam and Willow are holding hands.
Your attention snaps back to the Dragon King as he stirs.
A few of his Mates swoop down, picking him up.
They carry him off in the direction of their lair.
Suddenly, trees all over the forest starting to open up.
Inside their trunks you see... the villagers!
The other races notice too, and quickly go to help them.
You know they'll be ok without you, but you feel an urge...
You call out to one of the Dragon King's mates.
You beg her to help you check on the King. She obliges.
